# parallel-review-loop — N-reviewer code-debate loop.
# Terminates ONLY when all N reviewers APPROVE the same SHA. No manual exit.
# Default mix: 7×codex-xhigh + 1×claude-opus-high.

name: parallel-review-loop
version: "1.0"
description: N-reviewer parallel review loop, terminates on unanimous APPROVE on same SHA.

todos:
  - title: "Archive or remove stale REVIEW-*.md files before rendering reviewer prompts (gate: no prior-round REVIEW files remain in the worktree root)"
    priority: high
  - title: "Render canonical reviewer prompts from skills/parallel-review-loop/references/prompt-templates.md via render_review_prompts.py (gate: /tmp/review-{a..h}.md written)"
    depends_on: [1]
    priority: high
  - title: "Audit generated reviewer prompts with audit_review_prompts.py --letters a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h (gate: clean completeness audit before reviewer spawn)"
    depends_on: [2]
    priority: high
  - title: "Spawn N={{ N_REVIEWERS }} reviewers (default 7×codex-xhigh + 1×claude-opus-high) from audited canonical prompts (gate: all N spawned)"
    depends_on: [3]
    priority: high
  - title: "Collect N={{ N_REVIEWERS }} verdicts (APPROVE / REQUEST_CHANGES) (gate: N verdicts received)"
    depends_on: [4]
  - title: "Triage feedback per SOUL #1b — drop theoretical edges, defensive checks, scope creep, options nobody asked for (gate: triaged set written)"
    depends_on: [5]
    priority: high
  - title: "If all {{ N_REVIEWERS }} APPROVE on same SHA → mark this todo done to exit loop. Else: forward triaged feedback to existing implementer (gate: branch decision made)"
    depends_on: [6]
    priority: high
  - title: "If step 7 forwarded changes: implementer (kept alive) applies fixes, produces new SHA. Else: mark complete immediately as no-op (gate: new commit on branch OR step 7 was unanimous approve)"
    depends_on: [7]
  - title: "If step 8 produced a new SHA: kill every reviewer tmux session, archive or remove stale REVIEW-*.md files, rerun render plus audit with --letters a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h, and loop back by calling workloop_apply_template('parallel-review-loop', ...) again before any brand-new reviewer starts (gate: new round started OR previous round was unanimous and this todo is no-op)"
    depends_on: [8]
